/Assignment-1.title: Assignment 1
/Assignment-1.content:
$pf = 0.75$.
$50Hz$, $230Vrms$
$S = \frac{511448}{100} = 5114.48VA$ ### Question 1 Calculate $I_{rms}$ $$I_{rms} = \frac{S}{U_{rms}} = \frac{5114.48}{230} \approx 22.2A$$ Calculate P and Q of the load: $$P = U_{rms} * I_{rms} * cos(\varphi) = 230 * 22.2 * 0.75 = 3829.5W$$ $$\begin{gather}S^{2} = P^{2} + Q^{2}\newline5114.48^{2} = 382.95^{2} + Q^{2}\newline Q = \sqrt{5114.48^{2} - 382.95^{2}} = 3390.1 \text{var} \end{gather}$$ Calculate R and L values of the load: $$R = \frac{U_{rms}}{I_{rms}}=\frac{230}{22.2}=10.36\ohm$$ $$\begin{gather}pf=\frac{R}{|Z|}\newline 0.75=\frac{10.36}{|Z|}\newline |Z| = 13.81\end{gather}$$ $$X_{L}=\sqrt{|Z|^{2} - R^{2}}=9.13\ohm$$ $$L = \frac{X_{L}}{j\omega}=\frac{9.13}{j*2\pi*50}=\frac{9.13}{100\pi j}=0.02906j H$$

# > [Dashboard](_index.md) > [Differential Equation & Laplace](Differential%20Equation%20&%20Laplace/Differential%20Equation%20&%20Laplace.md)

Equation

An equation is an expression of a relationship between quantities, also called variables or unknowns.
A solution of an equation is a value for the variable(s) that makes the expression true after substitution.


Differential equation

A differential equation is an expression of a relationship between a quantity and the rate of change of that same quantity, or a relationship between a quantity and its own derivative.
A differential equation has two type of variable:
- The independant variable.
- The dependant variable.
